0:17:44.7,000 --> 0:17:46,000
I was in Tanzania, and I was in a classroom.

370
0:17:47.02,000 --> 0:17:5,000
This is me with a classroom of 11-year-olds.

371
0:17:51.3,000 --> 0:17:52,000
And I asked them, as I always do,

372
0:17:52.94,000 --> 0:17:54,000
"What do you want to be when you grow up?"

373
0:17:55.02,000 --> 0:17:56,000
Two raised their hands and said,

374
0:17:56.78,000 --> 0:17:58,000
"I want to be President of the World Bank."

375
0:17:58.82,000 --> 0:17:59,000
(Laughter)

376
0:18:00.66,000 --> 0:18:03,000
And just like you, my own team and their teachers laughed.

377
0:18:04.1,000 --> 0:18:05,000
But then I stopped them.

378
0:18:05.66,000 --> 0:18:07,000
I said, "Look, I want to tell you a story.

