0:18:23.54,000 --> 0:18:26,000
if he had visited Korea on that day and come to my classroom,

385
0:18:27.14,000 --> 0:18:28,000
that he would have thought

386
0:18:28.5,000 --> 0:18:3,000
that the future President of the World Bank

387
0:18:30.54,000 --> 0:18:31,000
was sitting in that classroom.

388
0:18:32.02,000 --> 0:18:34,000
Don't let anyone ever tell you

389
0:18:34.34,000 --> 0:18:36,000
that you cannot be President of the World Bank."

390
0:18:37.14,000 --> 0:18:38,000
Now -- thank you.

391
0:18:38.38,000 --> 0:18:39,000
(Applause)

392
0:18:39.98,000 --> 0:18:4,000
Let me leave you with one thought.

